  • Lord & Lady Jeavons
    Louth, United Kingdom393 contributions
    Great value for money
    This is one of the smaller hotels in Vegas and if you want glamour then this isn't the place for you, however, that said it was a good enough room with plenty of storage for our clothes, a kitchenette with a coffee machine, coffee pods, creamer and sugar, microwave, fridge and water, toiletries in the bathroom, hairdryer and iron. It was clean and housekeeping did an excellent job. The pool was quite small and basic but it was clean and fine. There was a room to print out our boarding passes or to do anything else we might have wanted to use a computer for, and there were vending and ice machines. The hotel was not expensive, had no hidden costs or resort fees and everything in our room was included in the price. There was a casino with a bar that was not expensive compared to other hotels, although the barman in the evening was extremely grumpy. There was an Outback restaurant on the premises which was nice, a Dennys, and a Wallmart. The hotel was in a good position right on the strip and in the middle of it all. The negatives were small in that it had a tiny reception area which meant always queuing for anything, and the room was a bit dark and had no outlook, but hey! Who goes to Vegas to hang out in their room?
    Visited September 2023
    Traveled as a couple
    Written October 17, 2023

    Great Location on the Strip
    I took a long time selecting my hotel for my trip of a lifetime to vegas, I didnt want a hotel that you had to walk a mile to get out of it and that was the reason I selected this hotel. Best decision I ever made, the hotel and pool are small but it was great, I walked down the stairs one way and was on the strip walked down another way and was in the pool, always had the pool to ourselves. The bar was well stocked with reasonably priced drinks, the lady was always around for our free drinks while gambling. Plenty of choice of food if I didnt want to go far. Staff really nice and always offered good advice. in the middle of the strip next to the big hotels (so glad I didnt stay in them) no resort fees whole holiday so cheap. Fabulous Stay at Casino Royale
Jun 2023
I have just come back from 9 nights at Casino Royale and I can honestly say it is a great budget hotel, I took my daughter who I thought might be disappointed it wasn't one of the big hotels but she said it was perfect, no walking for miles to get out the hotel, no staff trying to sell you something every two minutes and a pool to yourself.

The staff were great, Tina and the other lady on reception whose name I forgot sorry were fab, Tina even walk us to the entrance through the casino, room key needed to access the hotel so unlike the bigger hotels no one can come back with a key card. The casino floor staff were great. The reviews you read here do not reflect my stay at all, homeless in the area yes, the only time I saw one in the casino security moved them very quickly. Plenty of security walking around to make you feel safe if you had any doubts.

This is a great hotel for a central location in vegas right next door to the Ventitan opposite Mirage and Ceasars.

Is it true you don't have to pay for drinks here if you tip the bartenders.
Written November 3, 2019
Gary B
1 contribution
Tips don’t matter and have nothing to do with free drinks. Tips are your choice. What does matter is your Gambling play at the bar. If you play the machines at the bar drinks are free. However if if your play ebbs and slows down the bartender may decide to charge you. This happened to us and was unexpected. Basically you ask for a drink and don’t pay and the bar tender puts the bill in a glass on the bar. Out main complaint about this casino was the bar tender took our order and then charged the full price for the drink which we paid. What any other bar in Las Vegas would have done was said” I need to charge you for this one as your not playing enough”. If you play anywhere else in the casino (slots or table games) drinks are free and you typically just tip , if you don’t tip you may not see the waiter often.
